<title>USA: Citation president to resign.</title>
<headline>Citation president to resign.</headline>
<dateline>SAN JOSE, Calif. 1996-09-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>Citation Insurance Group said Monday President and Chief Executive Officer Donald Henderson is leaving the company to pursue other interests, in anticipation of the upcoming merger with Physicians Insurance Company of Ohio.</p>
<p>Citation said in a statement Chief Financial Officer Robert Erickson will become acting chief executive officer. The company also said it appointed Paul Bancroft as vice chairman of the board.</p>
<p>Henderson will act as a consultant to the company.</p>
